To search Public Records, use the property address or follow this APN format:

◆ Example: APN from Cyborg TISBM0008QB00000L00008 → 8-Q-8.

1. Take the first number after the initial zeros: 8
2. Take the letter right before "B0.": Q
3. Add the last 2 digits but if the penultimate one is 0, only add the last one: 8
4. Separate each part with a dash (-).

NO NEED TO PERFORM ADDRESS OVERRIDE IF ONLY THE CITY IS DIFFERENT.
* If you need to perform an address override in a condo with a building and unit, investigate if the same unit exists in a different building. If not, just include the unit in the override. Example: Address 433 Wild Irishman Rd has buildings 1, 2, and 3, and each one has different units. Building 1 has all the 100s, Building 2 has all the 200s, and Building 3 has all the 300s. In this case, just override with: 433 Wild Irishman Rd Unit 102. If, on the other hand, each building has the same units, include the building and unit in the override, e.g., 433 Wild Irishman Rd Unit 1-102.
